Exhibits Stolen From China’s Forbidden City Museum, CCTV Reports

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-05-11T14:35:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-11/exhibits-stolen-from-china-s-forbidden-city-museum-cctv-reports.html
Nine pieces on exhibit were stolen
from Beijing’s Forbidden City,  China Central Television  reported
its  website , citing Feng Nai’en, a museum spokesman.  The items, on loan from a Hong Kong museum for an
exhibition of furniture and handbags decorated with gold and
jewels, were probably stolen on the evening of May 8, CCTV
reported. Two items have been recovered and seven remaining
missing, the broadcaster said.  --Helen Yuan. Editor: Joshua Fellman  To contact the Bloomberg News staff on this story
Helen Yuan in Shanghai at 
 hyuan@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
